A new Assistant Inspector General (AIG) of police, Halilu Abubakar in charge of zone 3 headquarters, has assumed duty in Adamawa state. Abubakar at maiden interaction Tuesday in Yola, with commissioners of Taraba, Gombe and Adamawa states that comprises the zone assured that, issue of mistrust among officers and men  in the zone would be thing of the past. The AIG who assumed duty on January 6th  this year, rated security situation in the zone  as relative, compared to the security situation  in the country. “The zone in its renewed vigor in fighting criminals,  would apply new module operandi in arresting criminals and their perpetrators. “The zone under match, will appreciate people rendering information that could led to arrest of criminal. The AIG further said, the command would be serious about sending personnel for quick intervention units. “The personnel must be physically and mentally fit for the operation. “Criminal investigations must be conducted in a professional, manner inline with the relevant law.” The renewed vigor he added would be optimistic in addressing police extortion in the zone. 